<P><FONT SIZE="6"><B><FONT FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">What Is 
  The Card Verification Code ?</FONT></B></FONT></P>
<P><FONT FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" SIZE="2">The Card Verification 
  Code or CVC2 is an extra code printed on the reverse side of Credit Cards (Visa 
  and MasterCard) and on the front of the card for American Express. It's purpose 
  is to provide extra protection for the card holder in &quot;card not present&quot; 
  transactions (for example Internet transactions and Phone orders) as it ensures 
  that the purchaser is in possession of the card when placing the order. The 
  location of the code varies between cards, but these images should help you 
  locate the code.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" SIZE="2"><B><FONT SIZE="3">Visa 
  And MasterCard</FONT></B></FONT><BR>
 <FONT FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" SIZE="2">Visa and MasterCard 
 cards show the code as 3 or 4 digits printed on the back of the card usually 
 after the credit card number (or last four digits of the card number).</FONT></P>
